  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Food Security and WASH Response Project in Herat Province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">-Activity 1: Distribution of Standard Food Packages: WASSA will distribute (in-kind) standard food packages to 900 vulnerable households. 
-Activity 2: Distribution of Supplementary Food Packages: WASSA will distribute (in-kind) supplementary food packages to 200 pregnant and lactating women (PLW) and malnourished children under five years.
-Activity 3: Distribution of Hygiene Kits and Hygiene Promotion: WASSA will distribute (in-kind) standard hygiene kits to the 900 HHs.
-Activity 4: Conducting Hygiene and Covid-19 Prevention Sessions: WASSA will conduct/organise 45 community sessions on hygiene promotion and Covid-19 prevention. Each session will have 20 participants.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will respond to the most urgent food security and WaSH needs of 900 households (6,300 individuals), of which 70% will be IDP and 30% will be host community members, who have settled in the Injil District of Herat province. Specifically, the project will aim to:
-ER 1: Improve access to food through the distribution of standard food packages to 900 vulnerable households, with an additional 200 supplementary food (nutrition) packages for pregnant and lactating women (PLWs) and malnourished children under 5 years.
-ER 2: Improve hygiene condition through the distribution of hygiene kits to 900 vulnerable households and awareness raising sessions on hygiene and Covid-19 prevention.</narrative>
  </description>
